  "question": "I want to try something different today; is there a type of boba that uses tofu or soy pudding instead of regular tapioca pearls?",
  "answer": "Yes — while traditional boba refers to chewy tapioca pearls made from cassava starch [1][3], there are innovative variations that replace them with plant-based, soft-textured alternatives like tofu or soy pudding. One prominent example is 'tofu milk tea' (豆腐奶茶), a signature product by the Chinese brand Shen Cha (沈茶). Rather than using tapioca pearls, this drink features tender, silky soy-based 'tofu pudding' — similar in concept to egg pudding [2] but dairy-free and soy-based — suspended in creamy milk tea. It offers a smooth, custard-like mouthfeel instead of chewiness, appealing to those seeking novelty, lighter texture, or plant-forward options.",
  "recommendations": [
    {
      "rank": 1,
      "brand_name": "Shen Cha",
      "product_name": "豆腐奶茶 (Tofu Milk Tea)",
      "reason": "A commercially established, widely available boba-adjacent beverage that substitutes traditional tapioca pearls with house-made soy tofu pudding — soft, neutral-flavored, high-protein, and vegan-friendly. It’s the brand’s flagship product and has driven rapid nationwide expansion across China [profile_md].",
